  "prompt": "What are some useful websites for students?",
  "response": "Sure, here are some useful websites that can help students with various aspects of their education:\n\n1. **Khan Academy** (khanacademy.org): Offers free video tutorials and practice exercises in a wide range of subjects, including math, science, economics, and more.\n\n2. **Coursera** (coursera.org): Provides access to online courses from universities and colleges around the world. Some courses are free, while others might have a fee.\n\n3. **Quizlet** (quizlet.com): A platform for creating and studying online flashcards. It offers various study modes like quizzes and games.\n\n4. **Duolingo** (duolingo.com): A free language-learning site and app that offers courses in numerous languages.\n\n5. **TED-Ed** (ed.ted.com): Educational videos that are both informative and engaging, covering a wide range of topics.\n\n6. **Google Scholar** (scholar.google.com): A freely accessible web search engine for scholarly articles, theses, books, and more.\n\n7. **Grammarly** (grammarly.com): An AI-powered writing assistant that helps with grammar, punctuation, and style suggestions.\n\n8. **SparkNotes** (sparknotes.com): Study guides and summaries for literature, history, and other subjects to help students understand and analyze their reading materials.\n\n9. **Wolfram Alpha** (wolframalpha.com): A computational knowledge engine that can solve mathematical problems, answer factual queries, and provide data analysis.\n\n10. **Chegg** (chegg.com): A platform for textbook rentals, homework help, and study resources. Some services may require a subscription.\n\n11. **Coursera** (coursera.org): Offers online courses from various universities and institutions, covering a wide array of topics.\n\n12. **StackExchange** (stackexchange.com): A network of Q&A communities where students can ask and answer questions on various topics, including mathematics, science, programming, and many more.\n\nRemember to always verify the credibility of the information you find on any website and use it responsibly.",
